        "text": "<p>Lincoln Coal is planning a new coal mine, which will cost $430,000 to build. The mine will bring cash inflows of $200,000 annually over the next seven years. It will then cost $170,000 to close down the mine in the following year. Assume all cash flows occur at the end of the year. Alternatively, Lincoln Coal may choose to sell the site today. If Lincoln has a 16% required rate of return, the minimum price they should accept for the property is closest to:</p>",
