        "correctAnswerIndex": 2,
        "explanation": "The key is first identifying this as a NPV problem. The minimum price the company should accept for selling the property is the net present value of the mine if the company built and operated it. Next, the year of each cash flow must be property identified; specifically: CF0 = -$430,000; CF1-7 = +$200,000; CF8 = -$170,000. Entering these values into the cash flow worksheet: CF0 = -$430,000; C01 = 200,000; F01 = 7; C02 = -170,000; F02 = 1; I = 16; CPT NPV = 325,858.76."
