        "id": 1574698,
        "text": "<p>Fred Dean, CFA, has just taken a job as trader for LPC. One of his first assignments is to execute the purchase of a block of East Street Industries. While working with East Street on an assignment for his previous employer, he learned that East Street's sales have weakened and will likely be significantly below the LPC analyst's estimate, but no public announcement of this has been made. Which of the following actions would be the most appropriate for Dean to take according to the Standards?</p>",
