        "text": "<p>Victor Electronics, a manufacturer of electronic components, reports inventory using the FIFO costing method. In the prior period, Victor wrote its inventory down from cost of $2 million to its net realizable value of $1 million. During the current period, net realizable value increased to $4 million because of a shortage of computer chips. For the current period, Victor would most appropriately report an inventory value of:</p>",
