        "correctAnswerIndex": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Monetary policy is most effective when it can influence interest rates to manage aggregate demand. It is most effective when combatting inflation because there is no 'upper bound' on interest rates. Conversely, its effectiveness is limited in deflationary environments by the zero lower bound.</p>"
