        "text": "<p>An investor purchases a stock on January 1. The annual dividend payments for a stock investment for the next four years, beginning on December 31, are $50, $75, $100, and $125. Based on the cash flow additivity principle, the present value of this series of cash flows will be equivalent to the present value of a $50 annuity and the present value of what series of cash flows?</p>",
