        "correctAnswerIndex": 2,
        "explanation": "<p>Using Bayes' formula to update the probability:<br>P(economy does not expand | tech does not outperform) = P(economy does not expand and tech does not outperform) / P(tech does not outperform).<br>1. P(economy does not expand) = 1.00 - 0.60 = 0.40.<br>2. P(tech does not outperform | economy does not expand) = 1.00 - 0.10 = 0.90.<br>3. P(economy does not expand and tech does not outperform) = 0.90 x 0.40 = 0.36.<br>4. P(tech does not outperform | economy expands) = 1.00 - 0.70 = 0.30.<br>5. P(economy expands and tech does not outperform) = 0.30 x 0.60 = 0.18.<br>6. P(tech does not outperform) = 0.36 + 0.18 = 0.54.<br>7. P(economy does not expand | tech does not outperform) = 0.36 / 0.54 = 0.6667 or 67%.</p>"
