        "explanation": "<p>Using the total probability rule, we can compute P(B):<br>P(B) = [P(B | A) x P(A)] + [P(B | A<sup>C</sup>) x P(A<sup>C</sup>)]<br>P(B) = [0.5 x 0.4] + [0.2 x 0.6] = 0.32<br>Using Bayes' formula:<br>P(A | B) = [P(B | A) / P(B)] x P(A) = [0.5 / 0.32] x 0.4 = 0.625</p>"
