        "correctAnswerIndex": 1,
        "explanation": "Samples are often used in a simulation to estimate parameters for a population. Resampling is just taking the original observed sample and repeatedly drawing subsamples to estimate population parameters, such as mean and variance. (Module 6.1, LOS 6.c)"
