        "correctAnswerIndex": 1,
        "explanation": "With a large sample size (75) the z-statistic is used. The z-statistic is calculated by subtracting the hypothesized parameter from the parameter that has been estimated and dividing the difference by the standard error of the sample statistic. Here, the test statistic = (sample mean – hypothesized mean) / (sample standard deviation / (sample size)<sup>1/2</sup>) = (X – μ) / (σ / n<sup>1/2</sup>) = (57,000 – 54,000) / (1,300 / 75<sup>1/2</sup>) = (3,000) / (1,300 / 8.66) = 19.99. (Module 8.2, LOS 8.b)"
